text: Albert Nyman (22 November 1872 - 9 March 1924) was a Finnish diver. He competed in the men's plain high diving event at the 1912 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1872 births Category:1924 deaths Category:Finnish male divers Category:Olympic divers of Finland Category:Divers at the 1912 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from Helsinki
